1.	What is Parallel Bubble Sort? 
Parallel Bubble Sort is a parallel version of the Bubble Sort algorithm where multiple threads compar
and swap elements simultaneously to improve sorting speed. 
It uses parallel programming techniques such as OpenMP to divide sorting work among multiple processors/threads. 
“Parallel Bubble Sort performs sorting using multiple threads simultaneously.”  
2.	How does Parallel Bubble Sort work? 
Parallel Bubble Sort works by dividing comparison and swapping operations among multiple threads. 
Working 
1.	Compare adjacent elements. 
2.	Swap if elements are in wrong order. 
3.	Multiple comparisons happen simultaneously. 
4.	Repeat passes until array becomes sorted. 
Odd-Even Transposition Method 
Parallel Bubble Sort commonly uses: 
Odd phase ,Even phase 
Example 
Even Phase Compare: (0,1), (2,3), (4,5) 
Odd Phase Compare: (1,2), (3,4), (5,6) 
These comparisons occur in parallel.  
